{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f2128dc5-cab0-4770-98ba-414a1c5a3dbf","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01An2eWCjVk2mH8CNaWoRdYg","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Explaining .NET 10 changes"},"type":"function"}],"interactionId":"d12867f0-d817-4351-8c26-0ffe17dfc4b6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about breaking changes and new behaviors when upgrading from .NET 9 to .NET 10. Let me address each point:\n\n1. **[InlineArray] with explicit [StructLayout]** - In .NET 10, there's a breaking change where `[InlineArray]` types can no longer have explicit `[StructLayout]` attributes. The runtime now controls the layout of inline array types.\n\n2. **DriveInfo.DriveFormat on Linux** - In .NET 10, `DriveInfo.DriveFormat` on Linux now returns the file system type name (like \"ext4\") instead of the mount point path. \n\nCode that was comparing against specific strings may need updating. There are also several new NuGet-related behaviors: dependency pruning during restore can now produce NU1510 warnings, and audit checks have expanded to include transitive dependencies by default rather than just direct ones. Additionally, `FilePatternMatch.Stem` changed from nullable to non-nullable in .NET 10.","outputTokens":400,"requestId":"A445:2CEFFD:3A1246:4225E2:6A03D174"},"id":"ce072bf3-e6d9-40f8-908d-a1c71ff197b2","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:18:52.693Z","parentId":"764b4d6c-4bc2-4860-86f9-b1da434cf3dd"}
